body:
I got the same error. I thought the `pip3 --upgrade install` would install 1.1 by now?
I tried: 

```
PS C:\Users\kmand> pip3 install --upgrade tensorflow==1.1.0
Collecting tensorflow==1.1.0-rc2
  Downloading tensorflow-1.1.0rc2-cp35-cp35m-win_amd64.whl
...
tobuf>=3.2.0->tensorflow==1.1.0-rc2)
Installing collected packages: werkzeug, tensorf
  Found existing installation: tensorflow 1.0.1
    Uninstalling tensorflow-1.0.1:
      Successfully uninstalled tensorflow-1.0.1
Successfully installed tensorflow-1.1.0rc2 werkzeug-0.12.1
```

That looks strange!?

I also get 

```
>>> sess = tf.Session()
2017-04-21 17:10:34.351513: W c:\tf_jenkins\home\workspace\release-win\device\cpu\os\windows\tensorflow\core\platform\cpu_feature_guard.cc:45] The TensorFl
ow library wasn't compiled to use SSE instructions, but these are available on your machine and could speed up CPU computations.
```

Setting log level removes warning. Thanks

```
import os
os.environ['TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL']='2'
import tensorflow as tf
```
